ge_caption, description, import_source, import_external_id) VALUES ('2b097ea6-ea59-404f-b12d-d10958c4d116', 29, 'Necromantic healer and bone-reader', '{"Fiercely protective","Intellectually curious","Emotionally guarded","Pragmatically ruthless","Deeply empathetic"}', 'Raised by her Romani grandmother after her parents died in a plague, Isadora learned the old ways of bone magic and death healing in traveling caravans across Eastern European kingdoms. When her grandmother was executed for witchcraft, Isadora fled to study legitimate healing arts at a monastery, only to discover that death magic was the only thing that could save people conventional medicine couldn''t reach. She now walks the line between accepted healer and forbidden necromancer, using her powers to commune with the recently dead to solve murders and heal those touched by dark magic.', 'To prove that death magic can be a force for healing and justice, while seeking to uncover the truth about who betrayed her grandmother to the witch hunters', 'Her need to save everyone leads her to make increasingly dangerous bargains with death itself, risking her own humanity', 'An unshakeable moral compass that helps her navigate the ethical complexities of death magic', 'Fantasy', 'fa_sE2', '2025-10-18 01:52:25.413707', 'Female', '5''4"', 'Lean and wiry with calloused hands', 'Dark auburn with premature silver streaks', 'Hazel with gold flecks that seem to shift in candlelight', 'Olive complexion with a weathered quality from outdoor work', 'Sharp cheekbones, slightly crooked nose from an old break, expressive eyebrows', 'Intricate burn scar on left forearm in the shape of a raven, small ritual scars on fingertips', 'Isadora moves with the controlled grace of someone accustomed to dangerous work. Her auburn hair is often braided with small bones and metal trinkets. She has intelligent eyes that seem to catalog everything around her, and her hands are marked by both delicate scars from precise magical work and rougher damage from physical labor.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Human', 'Romani and Slavic heritage', 'she/her', 'The border city of Millbrook, operating from a converted apothecary shop', '', '{"Deceased grandmother Mileva who raised her and taught her death magic","Unknown parents who died in childhood plague","Estranged cousin Bogdan who became a witch hunter"}', '', 'Follows ancient Romani traditions honoring the ancestors, with some adapted Christian mysticism from monastery training', NULL, 'Isadora', 'Vargovich', 'Celestine', NULL, 'Dora to close friends, though few call her this', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A traveling caravan somewhere in the Carpathian Mountains', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'c5d694b4-3fbd-48c1-8061-e9ae1dcf30df', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Raised by her Romani grandmother after her parents died in a plague, Isadora learned the old ways of bone magic and death healing in traveling caravans across Eastern European kingdoms. When her grandmother was executed for witchcraft, Isadora fled to study legitimate healing arts at a monastery, only to discover that death magic was the only thing that could save people conventional medicine couldn''t reach. She now walks the line between accepted healer and forbidden necromancer, using her powers to commune with the recently dead to solve murders and heal those touched by dark magic.', NULL, NULL);
