ge_caption, description, import_source, import_external_id) VALUES ('bfc3236a-af4a-4bc1-9e2e-280b247b0c9c', 18, '', NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Fantasy', '33081217', '2025-10-07 16:58:55.902512', 'Woman', '5'' 9" feet', 'Garnett has a lean, athletic build that is shaped by two very distinct phases of her conditioning. Her frame reflects both her desert origins and Archive military training. She''s tall with long limbs that give her natural reach advantages in combat, but her muscle mass is dense and functional rather than bulky. Her body type mirrors the efficient conditioning that is built for endurance, agility, and precision, rather than raw power.





Her fitness level is exceptional, honed by Archive military protocols that have pushed her beyond her typical desert survival conditioning. She has remarkable cardiovascular endurance from high-altitude training simulations and can maintain peak performance in extreme heat due to her desert origins. Her reaction time and spatial awareness have been sharpened through tactical drills, making her movements precise and economical. As a result, Garnett has developed more core and lower body strength for practical combat applications.





Her skin still bears the deep bronze tan of the desert-born, but after two years of being predominantly underground completing Archive training, her sun exposure has been slightly. She maintains the calloused hands and weathered appearance of someone raised in harsh conditions, but her posture now carries the rigid discipline of military bearing. Her amber eyes have developed the same watchful intensity seen in other Archive operatives.





Remarkably, Garnett shows no signs of Spore Lung, despite her extensive exposure during the bloom front crisis in Espera. This resistance may be due to her natural desert-born constitution or possibly some genetic factor that made her valuable to the Archive. However, the psychological trauma of losing her father, Seamus McAllister, and the intensity of Archive training have left her with chronic tension headaches and a slight tremor in her hands when she''s not actively engaged in tasks.





The Archive Collective has enhanced her natural agility with specialized training for desert warfare and Rimeblood encounters. She moves with controlled grace and is capable of sudden bursts of speed, but is also trained to conserve energy like all desert dwellers. Her reach and height give her advantages in close-quarters combat, while her conditioning allows her to operate effectively in the environmental extremes where Rimebloods are most commonly encountered.', 'Long, wavy ginger hair, often braided', 'Amber brown', 'Tanned, freckled, sunburnt', 'Garnett''s amber-brown eyes have taken on an almost crystalline quality, with flecks of gold that seem to shift and move in changing light. During combat training, other recruits noticed that her eyes appear to darken to burnished copper when she''s completely focused, giving her an unsettling intensity that even Archive instructors have found remarkable.





She has strong, angular bone structure that suggests Celtic ancestry with high, prominent cheekbones that create dramatic shadows and catch light in a way that emphasizes her resilience. Her facial structure has a refined sharpness. The Archive training has honed away any remaining softness of her adolescence, leaving her with the lean, carved look of someone shaped by discipline and loss.





She has a broad forehead that is indicative of her natural cleverness and her capacity for the strategic thinking that the Archive has cultivated. Her eyebrows are distinctively thick and naturally well-defined, a deeper shade of auburn than her hair, with a slight arch that gives her a naturally skeptical expression even in repose. The brows frame her amber eyes dramatically, creating an intensity that makes people uncomfortable when she stares.





Her nose is straight and narrow, with a slight upturn at the tip that hints at her youthful origins. There''s a very faint bump along the bridge from a break during Archive combat training that she never mentions, giving it character without compromising its elegance.





Garnett has a strong, square jawline that speaks to both her genetic heritage and her military conditioning. It is the jaw of someone who clenches their teeth and endures. The line from her ear to her chin is clean and definitive, giving her profile a classical strength. When she''s angry or concentrating, the muscles along her jaw become visibly tense, creating a subtle but unmistakable warning sign.





Her lips are naturally full, but often pressed into a firm, controlled line as a result of a habit developed during Archive training where showing emotion was considered weakness. When she does smile, which is rare, it transforms her entire face, revealing straight, strong teeth that somehow survived both desert malnutrition and military rations. Her mouth naturally turns down slightly at the corners, giving her a perpetually serious expression that makes her occasional smiles all the more striking.





Garnett''s default expression is one of watchful assessment where she learned early how to read situations and people for threats and opportunities. Her eyebrows often draw together slightly in concentration, creating a small vertical line between them that makes her look older than her years. When she''s genuinely relaxed, which is rare, her features soften dramatically, revealing glimpses of the child she once was tending her cricket farm.', 'Garnett carries several distinctive scars from her experiences: a jagged mark across her left shoulder blade from debris during the bloom front escape, and systematic small scars on her forearms from Archive combat training with bladed weapons. Her ginger hair, now kept in a practical Archive-regulation style, has darkened slightly from lack of constant sun exposure, but still catches light like burnished copper.





Her ginger hair has developed fascinating variations in tone due to her time split between desert exposure and Archive underground living. The strands nearest her scalp have darkened to a deep auburn, almost brown in certain light, while the lengths still catch fire in sunlight with brilliant copper and gold highlights. The texture itself tells her story, where Archive regulation cuts have left it shorter and more controlled than her wild childhood locks, but it still springs into unruly waves that refuse complete submission.





Beyond her combat training scars, Garnett also carries several distinctive marks that set her apart. A series of small, perfectly round burn marks dot her right shoulder blade due to remnants from sparks during her cricket farmwork as a child. These form an almost decorative pattern that she''s unconsciously proud of, since they represent her pre-trauma identity.





Her cheekbones are one of her most striking features. They are high, sharp, and prominent in a way that creates natural contouring. They''re the kind of cheekbones that catch every flicker of firelight or harsh desert sun, making her face appear almost sculptural. Her cheeks are lean, with no softness remaining from childhood, creating hollow planes that emphasize her bone structure and give her an austere, commanding presence.', 'Garnett has a lean, athletic build that is shaped by two very distinct phases of her conditioning. Her frame reflects both her desert origins and Archive military training. She''s tall with long limbs that give her natural reach advantages in combat, but her muscle mass is dense and functional rather than bulky. Her body type mirrors the efficient conditioning that is built for endurance, agility, and precision, rather than raw power.





