The Archive Collective has enhanced her natural agility with specialized training for desert warfare and Rimeblood encounters. She moves with controlled grace and is capable of sudden bursts of speed, but is also trained to conserve energy like all desert dwellers. Her reach and height give her advantages in close-quarters combat, while her conditioning allows her to operate effectively in the environmental extremes where Rimebloods are most commonly encountered.', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '145 lbs', '', NULL, 'She/Her', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Espera', '', NULL, 'Garnett', 'McAllister', 'Evelyn', '', 'Cricket', 'Lieutenant', '', NULL, 'March 19th, 2034 (Year 13 A.V.)', 'Espera', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '', NULL, '{English}', NULL, '', 'Garnett''s bronze skin carries a unique dual texture that incorporates the original weathered leather-quality of desert life layered with the subtle smoothness that comes from Archive conditioning. Her skin has an almost contradictory quality where patches of Archive-softened skin meet areas that were carved by wind and salt.





The most striking feature is her freckle constellation that is scattered across her nose and cheeks, cascading in dense clusters down her shoulders, forearms, and collarbone like rust-coloured stardust. These freckles have an unusual depth to them, with some appearing almost three-dimensional against her skin, as if the desert sun-branded each one individually.





Most unusually, she has developed what appear to be faint stretch marks along her inner arms and across her shoulders. This is not from weight changes, but from the rapid muscle development that occurred during her intensive Archive training. At first glance they might be mistaken for pale scars, but they have a silvery quality that catches light differently.





Her hands tell perhaps the most complex story because they have retained the original calluses from cricket farmin, but have been joined by new ones from weapons training. This has created an unusual pattern of toughened skin. Her fingertips retain unusual sensitivity despite the calluses, a remnant of her delicate work with small insects and mechanisms in Espera.





Unlike other desert dwellers, Garnett shows no signs of the chronic dehydration lines or sun damage that would be expected for someone her age. The Archive''s controlled environment seems to have preserved some of her youthful skin quality while her genetics have protected her from typical spore exposure effects. This creates an unsettling contrast where she looks both older and younger than her years simultaneously.', NULL, 'Garnett carries several distinctive scars from her experiences: a jagged mark across her left shoulder blade from debris during the bloom front escape, and systematic small scars on her forearms from Archive combat training with bladed weapons. Her ginger hair, now kept in a practical Archive-regulation style, has darkened slightly from lack of constant sun exposure, but still catches light like burnished copper.





