Beyond her combat training scars, Garnett also carries several distinctive marks that set her apart. A series of small, perfectly round burn marks dot her right shoulder blade due to remnants from sparks during her cricket farmwork as a child. These form an almost decorative pattern that she''s unconsciously proud of, since they represent her pre-trauma identity.





Her cheekbones are one of her most striking features. They are high, sharp, and prominent in a way that creates natural contouring. They''re the kind of cheekbones that catch every flicker of firelight or harsh desert sun, making her face appear almost sculptural. Her cheeks are lean, with no softness remaining from childhood, creating hollow planes that emphasize her bone structure and give her an austere, commanding presence.', NULL, NULL, 'Garnett displays an extraordinary resistance to environmental hazards. She has complete immunity to Spore Lung despite extensive exposure during the bloom front crisis, suggesting either genetic resistance or early exposure that built immunity. The Archive has noted this trait and enhanced it through specialized conditioning, making her invaluable for operations in contaminated zones.





Her years tending cricket farms have developed an almost supernatural ability to read small-scale biological systems. Garnett can assess the health of any contained ecosystem instantly, from insect populations to plant growth to water quality. This extends to recognizing early signs of Verdant contamination, Rimeblood presence, or environmental toxicity, long before standard detection methods would register threats.





Three years of intensive military conditioning have sharpened her natural desert-born reflexes into something approaching preternatural. She can react to multiple simultaneous threats with calculated precision, making her exceptionally dangerous in close-quarters combat. Her reaction time is fast enough that other soldiers sometimes wonder if she''s anticipating attacks rather than simply responding to them.





Growing up in scarcity and learning Archive efficiency protocols has given her an uncanny ability to maximize limited resources. She can make water, food, ammunition, or fuel last impossibly long, often finding ways to stretch supplies that confound even experienced Archive quartermasters. This isn''t just careful rationing, as she seems to intuitively understand how to optimize consumption without compromising performance.





Her desert origins combined with Archive conditioning have given her unusual control over her body''s thermoregulation processes and metabolism. She can function at peak performance in extreme heat or cold, requires less water than should be possible, and can slow her metabolism during resource shortages in ways that border on controlled hibernation.





The Archive has trained her natural analytical abilities to an extraordinary degree. She can read battlefield situations, enemy movement patterns, and environmental changes with an accuracy that seems almost prescient. This makes her invaluable for predicting Rimeblood behaviour and coordinating defensive strategies.





A combination of her childhood cricket-farming patience and Archive stealth training has made her capable of moving with complete silence across any terrain. She can approach within striking distance of most targets without detection, earning her the nickname "Cricket" among other Archive operatives • both for her farming background and her ability to appear and disappear like an insect.', 'Garnett displays an extraordinary resistance to environmental hazards. She has complete immunity to Spore Lung despite extensive exposure during the bloom front crisis, suggesting either genetic resistance or early exposure that built immunity. The Archive has noted this trait and enhanced it through specialized conditioning, making her invaluable for operations in contaminated zones.





