A combination of her childhood cricket-farming patience and Archive stealth training has made her capable of moving with complete silence across any terrain. She can approach within striking distance of most targets without detection, earning her the nickname "Cricket" among other Archive operatives • both for her farming background and her ability to appear and disappear like an insect.', NULL, 'Garnett wears a modified Archive military uniform that is adapted for desert and extreme temperature operations. Her base layer consists of a fitted, moisture-wicking undershirt in Archive regulation charcoal grey that is designed to regulate body temperatures during extreme weather conditions. Over this, she wears a tactical vest in muted olive drab that is lighter than standard Archive issue due to her desert specialization, but is reinforced with trauma plates at vital points for her protection.





Her pants are Archive-regulation fitted cargo trousers in desert tan, made from a specialized fabric that resists both temperature extremes and spore contamination. Unlike standard issue, hers have extra reinforcement at the knees and seat from her childhood habit of crouching while tending crickets, a practical modification that the Archive pragmatically allowed.





Her most distinctive piece is a modified Archive environmental suit jacket that can be worn open during normal operations or sealed for hostile environments. The jacket is a unique copper-bronze colour that is used as an Archive experiment in desert camouflage to complement her ginger hair. It features internal heating elements for Rimeblood encounters and cooling vents for desert operations.





She wears Archive-issued combat boots that have been modified with additional insulation and specialized grip plates for ice-covered surfaces. The boots still bear traces of salt stains from her Espera origins that she hasn''t bothered to remove.





Around her neck, she wears a regulation Archive identification chain, but tucked beneath her shirt is a small vial of salt from Espera''s flats; it is the only personal memento she allowed herself to keep. The vial is cork-stopped and wrapped in a piece of fabric from her childhood cricket-farming apron.





Her utility belt is Archive-standard but customized for her specialization. She carries Archive-issue tactical gloves designed for extreme temperature operations, with textured fingertips that allow for precise manipulation even when numb from the cold. The gloves can be heated internally or cooled as needed.





Despite Archive regulations, Garnett has made subtle personal modifications to her gear. The copper wire threading through her equipment harness is twisted in patterns that mirror the structure of cricket wing-cases, serving as an unconscious homage to her farming days in the form of a practical organizational system.





Her hair is kept in regulation Archive style , pulled back in a tight braid that won''t interfere with equipment, but is secured with a small copper clip that she crafted herself: another subtle rebellion against complete institutional uniformity.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0fe4e254-02d1-4a14-9046-6b3aefe17a89', NULL, 'https://wa-cdn.nyc3.digitaloceanspaces.com/user-data/production/ee136645-e433-489b-a47f-314d4364e12e/uploads/images/a4fe0b065c9b6f795801ffe2eb9f2c0a.png', 'crossblossom_Garnetts_amber-brown_eyes_have_taken_on_an_almos_2e2bb78c-5ebc-4501-800d-6a29a8353c86_0.png', 'In the harsh sanctuary of Espera, where the salt flats stretch like bone-white scars beneath an unforgiving sun, Garnett Collins moves through her days with the quiet devotion of someone already ancient in her understanding of survival. At eight years old, she carries herself with the careful precision of a child who has never known abundance, her small frame weathered by the desert''s relentless touch, yet unbroken by its constant harsh demands.





Her hair catches the desert light like burnished copper, long waves the colour of rust and flame that she often keeps pulled back in practical braids to keep the strands from interfering with her work. The sun has painted constellations of freckles across her nose and cheeks, each one a testament to the hours she has spent bent over her cricket enclosures under the open desert sky. Her skin bears the deep tan of the desert-born, bronzed and slightly roughened from constant exposure to wind and salt, marked here and there with the tiny scratches that come from handling wooden crates and wire mesh.





When she looks up from her work, her amber-brown eyes hold depths that seem too knowing for her age. They are the colour of desert honey when it catches the light, warm and alert, constantly scanning her small domain for signs of trouble or triumph. In those eyes lies the intensity of a child who has learned that her careful attention means the difference between feast and famine for her community.





The soft chirping that emanates from her wooden enclosures serves as Espera''s unlikely lullaby, a gentle percussion that speaks of protein and perseverance in a world where both are precious commodities. Garnett moves among her charges with the reverence of a keeper of sacred things, understanding instinctively that in her small hands rests not just the welfare of insects, but the continued survival of everyone she has ever known. In her quiet dedication lies the fierce heart of the Saltfolk themselves, shaped by the desert''s harsh wisdom, teaching her that tenderness and toughness are not opposites, but partners in the dance of endurance. But this was before she was recruited by The Archive Collective as a child soldier to fight in the war against the Rootbound and the sudden emergence of Rimeblood packs threatening Frostborne populations.', NULL, NULL);
