gh to leave permanent records, fingertips bearing the grey-white mineral staining that no amount of scrubbing can fully erase. These hands move with the deliberate certainty of someone who has learned to read stone by touch, fingers that can assess the stability of a tunnel wall or the quality of a salt deposit through texture alone.





