ge_caption, description, import_source, import_external_id) VALUES ('63cd4635-475b-42be-a3c7-e15625d4c27e', 32, 'Industrial hygienist specializing in workplace air quality assessment', '{"methodically cautious","deeply empathetic","quietly stubborn"}', 'Raised by her Norwegian grandfather after her parents died in a factory explosion when she was eight. Her grandfather, a former shipbuilder, immigrated to Minnesota in the 1960s and raised her with rigid safety protocols that bordered on paranoia. She spent her childhood learning to identify hazards everywhere - loose railings, chemical smells, structural weaknesses. This hypervigilance helped her excel academically but left her struggling with intimate relationships. She chose her profession to prevent others from experiencing her childhood trauma, but constantly battles between her need to protect people and her recognition that absolute safety is impossible.', 'To prevent workplace disasters while learning to live with acceptable levels of risk in her personal life', 'Her obsessive need for safety and control pushes people away and prevents her from taking necessary emotional risks', 'Exceptional ability to identify dangers others miss and genuine care for worker safety', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-24 21:53:38.912177', 'female', '5''4"', 'Lean and wiry with calloused hands from fieldwork', 'Ash blonde, usually braided back practically', 'Pale blue with intense focus', 'Fair with slight tan lines from safety equipment', 'Sharp cheekbones, thin lips that rarely smile, expressive eyebrows', 'Small scar above left eyebrow from childhood accident, callused fingertips from handling equipment', 'Tamsin has the compact, efficient build of someone who spends time in industrial environments. Her pale blue eyes seem to constantly assess her surroundings, and she moves with deliberate precision. Her ash blonde hair is always secured away from her face, and she favors practical clothing in muted colors. Despite her serious demeanor, there''s a gentleness in how she handles her equipment and speaks to workers that reveals her underlying compassion.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
