ge_caption, description, import_source, import_external_id) VALUES ('4c166a88-04d4-4ef3-9227-b9f09154e85a', 32, 'Industrial safety inspector for offshore wind farms', '{methodical,guilt-ridden,"fiercely protective"}', 'Born to a Finnish mother and Ethiopian father who met while working for an international environmental NGO in Helsinki. Raised primarily by her maternal grandfather after her parents died in a helicopter crash during a research expedition when she was twelve. Her grandfather, a former shipyard worker, instilled in her a deep respect for industrial safety protocols. She became obsessed with preventing accidents after witnessing a coworker''s fall at her first job. Despite her expertise, she carries crushing guilt over a minor oversight three years ago that contributed to a colleague''s injury, leading her to become almost compulsively thorough in her work while struggling with anxiety about making another mistake.', 'To prevent any workplace accident from ever happening under her watch again', 'Paralyzing perfectionism that stems from guilt, causing her to second-guess herself and alienate colleagues with excessive oversight', 'Unwavering commitment to protecting others, even at personal cost', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-24 21:56:11.710747', 'female', '5''9"', 'Lean and athletic from years of climbing industrial structures', 'Dark brown with natural auburn highlights, usually pulled back in a practical ponytail', 'Warm amber eyes with flecks of green', 'Medium brown with golden undertones', 'Angular cheekbones inherited from her mother, full lips from her father, and a small scar through her left eyebrow from childhood', 'Rope burn scars on both palms, small compass tattoo behind her right ear', 'Asha carries herself with quiet authority, her posture always alert and ready. Her hands are calloused from years of technical work, and she habitually checks her safety equipment multiple times before use. She has a habit of unconsciously touching the compass tattoo when concentrating, and her eyes constantly scan for potential hazards even in casual settings.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);


