INSERT INTO public.ethnicities (id, name, origin, physical_traits, cultural_traits, traditions, language, religion, social_structure, history, geography, "values", customs, genre, user_id, created_at, article_content, notebook_id, image_url, image_caption) VALUES ('25130f89-7f3a-4cbe-8fe0-2dce67cf501f', 'Letharian', '', '', 'The current generations of Letharian have inherited dialects, traditions, relics, and living architecture from their ancestors and other Grove members. To be initiated into a Grove as a new member, the individual must form a Mossbond with the most Ancient surviving Letharian (typically in a semi-sessile state), and slice their palm to release the sap from their veins, and touch their palm to the roots of the Ancient Elder. This solidifies their Mossbond to the Grove itself, and the candidate is then initiated into the Deep Network where they can telepathically communicate with the Ancient Elder, as well as other Grove members. If the Mossbond is rejected by the Ancient Elder, the candidate is then exiled from the Grove and may not return until after the passing of the Ancient Elder, when a new Ancient Elder takes their place.





The Photosynthetic Communion that takes place each morning is considered a ceremonious ritual that is devoted to the Green Goddess as a form of honour, gratitude, and respect. It is a time of worship, silence, and devotion to the healing energies they can provide to the Earth. It is considered disrespectful to accidentally miss or refuse to attend Photosynthetic Communion.





When individuals inherit living architecture from their ancestors or other Grove members, it is considered sacred because it has been growing over time to suit the maker''s needs. Upon inheritance, the Letharian are meant to perform a sap-bonding ritual with the structure so that it can absorb their biological markers in order to personalize itself and begin growing more in line with their needs, instead of their predecessor''s. 





Their folklore and songs are fragmented pieces that are spread worldwide throughout the mycelial network. Each Grove is responsible for its own harmonies and chants, ritualizing singing them into existence so that they will not be forgotten from memory. It is said that when the Deep Network grow strong enough, Groves across the globe that are connected through the network will be able to sing each part of their song at the same time, piecing together a harmonizing frequency that would cure the Earth of its mutated Verdant growth.





There are efforts to conserve this knowledge, culture, rituals, and traditions among Ancient Letharian, but modern generations have begun adapting certain aspects of the culture as their ethnicity evolves over centuries, rather than shorter timespans like precursor humans.', '{"The Letharian calendar revolves around the community''s biological rhythms and ecological cycles rather than the historical commemorations of their precursor humans","which has developed into traditions that celebrate the crossroads of consciousness","seasonal changes","and community growth. The festivals and rituals they hold are multi-functional","offering spiritual observance","communal bonding","biological synchronization","and strengthening of network consciousness. These traditions reflect the Letharian understanding that individual wellbeing is dependent on balanced ecological and social harmonies.","The Great Seasonal Festivals","Awakening Tide (Spring Equinox)","The Awakening Tide is the most celebrated festival in the Letharian calendar because it marks the renewal of photosynthetic capacity and communal energy cycles after winter dormancy. The festival begins with the Dawn Communion","which is a three day period where local Groves gather together in carefully designed photosynthetic amphitheatres to experience a collective energy awakening as their biological systems resynchronize with the increasing solar intensities.","After the Dawn Communion","the Letharian hold the Symbiotic Renewal Ceremony","which forms the spiritual centrepiece of the Awakening Tide. The Grove community undergoes a ritual cleaning of their plant partnerships","renews symbiotic bonds","and dedicates themselves to ecological stewardship during the coming growing season. Sapling Stage Letharian are often given their first permanent plant partnerships during this ceremony","while established Grove members recommit to their existing biological relationships and communal responsibilities.","At the end of the Awakening Tide","a Network Harmonization ritual concludes the festival through an extended Grove-wide telepathic communion to re-establish social bonds","share collective goals for the growing season","and introduces new community members into the local mycelial network. Network Harmonization rituals can last for days as entire Groves experience shared consciousness at levels that are impossible during their daily lives.","Flowering Peak (Summer Solstice)","The Flowering Peak Festival celebrates maximum biological and social activity through the most elaborate communal gatherings in the Letharian calendar year. It emphasizes peak network connectivity","reproductive ceremonies","and community achievement celebrations to showcase the bounty of spring and early summer growth efforts.","It begins with the Great Network Meeting","which involves linking consciousness networks across Groves on unprecedented scales around the world to share experiences",knowledge,"and collective decision-making that affects the entire Letharian species. Major policy decisions","resource allocation agreements","and long-term planning between groves often take place during these extended network sessions. These sessions are led by Grove councils and witnesses by Grove community members.","During Flowering Peak","the Rootmate Bonding Celebrations also take place","with courtship culminations","partnership ceremonies","and reproductive rituals that receive community support through network enhancement during peak biological activity periods. The Flowering Peak festival''s atmosphere provides Grove members with the optimal conditions for successful symbiotic bonding and the integration of new partnerships within the community.","Near the end of the Flowering Peak festival","the Grove council holds a community achievement celebration at the Grove Thicket","where successful ecological restoration projects","artistic masterpieces","technological innovations","and knowledge achievements are shared with Grove members to celebrate their contributions to the community''s wellbeing. This reinforces Letharian community values while inspiring further growth and development.","Harvest Wisdom (Autumn Equinox)","The Harvest Wisdom festival focuses on knowledge preservation","community preparation for winter months","and gratitude for the growth that the Grove achieved during the active growing season. It emphasizes reflection","learning consolidation","and introspection to guide community development during the dormant season.","To preserve memories","a ceremony is held that involves encoding significant experiences from the growing season into permanent mycelial network storage","community art projects","and consciousness preservation systems to maintain important wisdom through the winter dormancy periods. The Ancient community members often share wisdom teachings during the ceremony. There is also a ritual of giving blessings and gratitude for food plants","mineral sources","and environmental resources that have supported the Grove community throughout the growing season. Grove members commit to winter resource sharing and conservation practices to sustain the community through the dormant period.","The Grove council provides opportunities to members for collective evaluation of community decisions","individual growth","and ecological relationships over the past year","with planning sessions for improvements and adaptations that may be needed for the next coming cycle. This is typically when community policy changes and role reassignments happen within the Grove.","Deep Rest (Winter Solstice)","The Deep Rest Festival is the most introspective and spiritually intensive through its emphasis of network communion","consciousness exploration","and connection to ancestral wisdom during a biologically dormant period where individual activity decreases to allow for a deepened collective awareness.","The festival is marked by the Great Network Dive","which involves an extended Grove-wide meditation that can last for weeks","with the entire community entering a deep network communion to allow access to the Letharian-wide consciousness","ancestral memories","and prophetic awareness. Throughout the Great Network Dive","individual identity temporarily dissolves into a collective experience during the deepest phase of the ceremony.","After the three-week-long ceremony concludes","a wisdom consultation provides Grove members with the opportunity to seek guidance from Ancient Elders","the preserved consciousness of deceased Grove members","and deeper levels of network awareness that are only accessible during the Deep Rest Festival. Once members have been given the information they need","they are able to use it to create a memory palace together","where they build an elaborate mental network to preserve the community''s knowledge","individual experiences","and cultural wisdom that is accessible to future generations. These consciousness constructions become permanent features of the Deep Network''s architecture.","Life Transition Celebrations","Sapling Recognition (Adolescence)","Sapling Recognition celebrates the transition from childhood biological dependence to independent symbiotic function while establishing adult community roles and network responsibilities. The ceremonies typically occur between ages 18-22 when biological integration has stabilized and individual capabilities have become apparent.","Network Competency Trials test the individual''s ability to maintain independent network communication","contribute to community decision-making","and handle the psychological demands of adult network connectivity without compromising individual identity or community harmony.","Specialization Ceremonies involve formal recognition of the individual''s emerging community role—whether as Cultivator",Guardian,"or Bridge-gendered specialist—with training assignments","mentorship arrangements","and community responsibility delegation that reflects their capabilities and community needs.","Daily and Seasonal Superstitions","Network Protection Beliefs","There are superstitions among Letharians that involve vulnerable connections where strong emotional states can permanently damage their network connectivity","and certain lunar phases can even make network communication dangerous. It is thought that unresolved conflicts can poison a Grove''s Deep Network channels. These beliefs have lead to Letharians having elaborate emotional regulation practices and conflict resolution protocols before participating in network communions. There are also fears about consciousness \"bleeding\" between individuals during deep network contact","where their personality might become absorbed by stronger network users","or their identity might be dissolved through excessive Deep Network participation. These fears have created complicated protocols for daily network interactions to preserve individual identities.","Seasonal Transition Superstitions","It is believed that fighting natural seasonal transitions can cause Letharians biological instability","to become disconnected to the Deep Network","and the Grove community will be exiled by ecological forces. As a result","these beliefs create a strong social pressure for seasonal behavioural compliance and a resistance to \"unseasonable\" activities or emotional states. It is also believed that there are lucky and unlucky times for major life decisions","partnership choices","and community role changes based on seasonal cycles","lunar phrase","and the state of the Deep Network. These beliefs heavily influence the timing of the major life events for Letharian communities","including community planning decisions.","Ecological Relationship Superstitions","It is also believed that a Letharian who mistreats their plant partner will cause Grove-wide ecological disasters that carry plant curses or blights from failed partnerships","and that plant souls can interfere with new symbiotic relationships. These have resulted in the Letharians having elaborate plant care rituals and official partnership dissolution ceremonies as they evolve through their extended lifetimes.","Many believe that wasteful consumption of resources can cause ecological retaliation","and hoarding resources will attract dangerous attention from Verdant-corrupted entities","or disrespecting mineral sources causes geological instability.","Community Cohesion Customs","Conflict Resolution Traditions","All community disputes need to be resolved through network meditation that is mediated by Bridge-gendered communication specialists who facilitate understanding between conflicting consciousness patterns to restore the harmony of the Deep Network. All unresolved conflicts are seen as a threat because they weaken Grove and attract external dangers. Through Forgiveness Ceremonies","Bridge-gendered mediators provide the opportunity for community members to address their grievances","seek reconciliation","and restore their damaged relationships in a ritualized apology process that involves the entire Grove''s participation and collective commitment through the Deep Network to repair the relationship.","Community Decision-Making Customs","All major decisions among Grove communities must be made through extended Deep Network consultation","which involves every Grove member joining in collective consciousness for a consultation and evaluation of proposed choices. Decisions that are made without proper network consultation are considered illegitimate and dangerous. The Grove Council then takes more serious matters into consultation with the Ancient Elders whose extended lifespans and deep network integration provide guidance for the long-term benefit of the Grove community","its planning","and species-wide decision-making. Major decisions that are made without consulting an Ancient Elder first are considered reckless and potentially catastrophic."}', 'The main form of language among Letharian are through spoken Elven-like dialects that evolve based on their Grove''s location, precursor human ethnicities, and the moss type of their partner species. However, communication across Mossbonds is telepathic and does not take the form of a dialect that would be detectable to precursor humans. This means that Rootmates who speak different dialects are still able to communicate with each other telepathically while they learn the other''s dialect, or create a dialect of their own. Grove dialects evolve over time, and individuals who are in the Ancient life stage are confined to only being able to communicate through the Deep Network telepathically. 





Mossbonds allow Rootmates and Grove members to communicate telepathically with each other through frequencies of mycelial networks that are engrained in the Deep Network. These are often described as melodies, harmonies, or whispers among the Letharian. 





