voided — thought to represent the “creeping hunger” of the Verdancy.","Other Specific Customs","• Birth: Newborns are anointed with a smear of brine across the forehead","“marking them as children of scarcity.”","• Death: The dead are salted before burial or left to desiccate naturally in salt caverns. A ritual spill of water accompanies funerals.","• Coming of Age: At age thirteen","a youth must survive a night alone in the salt flats with only a gourd of water and a salt pouch. Returning marks entry into adulthood.","• Trade Days: When caravans arrive","stalls spring up with roasted insects","prickly pear skewers","and embroidered cloth patches. These days are half-market",half-festival,"often accompanied by music and storytelling."}', 'Fantasy', '33081217', '2025-10-07 14:47:47.303069', NULL, '0fe4e254-02d1-4a14-9046-6b3aefe17a89', '', '');
