ively understand how to optimize consumption without compromising performance.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nHer desert origins combined with Archive conditioning have given her unusual control over her body''s thermoregulation processes and metabolism. She can function at peak performance in extreme heat or cold, requires less water than should be possible, and can slow her metabolism during resource shortages in ways that border on controlled hibernation.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nThe Archive has trained her natural analytical abilities to an extraordinary degree. She can read battlefield situations, enemy movement patterns, and environmental changes with an accuracy that seems almost prescient. This makes her invaluable for predicting Rimeblood behaviour and coordinating defensive strategies.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nA combination of her childhood cricket-farming patience and Archive stealth training has made her capable of moving with complete silence across any terrain. She can approach within striking distance of most targets without detection, earning her the nickname \"Cricket\" among other Archive operatives • both for her farming background and her ability to appear and disappear like an insect.", "valuesEthicsMorals": "", "genderUnderstanding": null, "physicalDescription": "Garnett has a lean, athletic build that is shaped by two very distinct phases of her conditioning. Her frame reflects both her desert origins and Archive military training. She''s tall with long limbs that give her natural reach advantages in combat, but her muscle mass is dense and functional rather than bulky. Her body type mirrors the efficient conditioning that is built for endurance, agility, and precision, rather than raw power.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nHer fitness level is exceptional, honed by Archive military protocols that have pushed her beyond her typical desert survival conditioning. She has remarkable cardiovascular endurance from high-altitude training simulations and can maintain peak performance in extreme heat due to her desert origins. Her reaction time and spatial awareness have been sharpened through tactical drills, making her movements precise and economical. As a result, Garnett has developed more core and lower body strength for practical combat applications.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nHer skin still bears the deep bronze tan of the desert-born, but after two years of being predominantly underground completing Archive training, her sun exposure has been slightly. She maintains the calloused hands and weathered appearance of someone raised in harsh conditions, but her posture now carries the rigid discipline of military bearing. Her amber eyes have developed the same watchful intensity seen in other Archive operatives.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nRemarkably, Garnett shows no signs of Spore Lung, despite her extensive exposure during the bloom front crisis in Espera. This resistance may be due to her natural desert-born constitution or possibly some genetic factor that made her valuable to the Archive. However, the psychological trauma of losing her father, Seamus McAllister, and the intensity of Archive training have left her with chronic tension headaches and a slight tremor in her hands when she''s not actively engaged in tasks.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nThe Archive Collective has enhanced her natural agility with specialized training for desert warfare and Rimeblood encounters. She moves with controlled grace and is capable of sudden bursts of speed, but is also trained to conserve energy like all desert dwellers. Her reach and height give her advantages in close-quarters combat, while her conditioning allows her to operate effectively in the environmental extremes where Rimebloods are most commonly encountered.", "physicalPresentation": null, "languageFluencyAccent": null, "marksPiercingsTattoos": null, "speechParticularities": null, "affiliatedOrganizations": null, "distinctiveBodyFeatures": "Garnett''s bronze skin carries a unique dual texture that incorporates the original weathered leather-quality of desert life layered with the subtle smoothness that comes from Archive conditioning. Her skin has an almost contradictory quality where patches of Archive-softened skin meet areas that were carved by wind and salt.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nThe most striking feature is her freckle constellation that is scattered across her nose and cheeks, cascading in dense clusters down her shoulders, forearms, and collarbone like rust-coloured stardust. These freckles have an unusual depth to them, with some appearing almost three-dimensional against her skin, as if the desert sun-branded each one individually.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nMost unusually, she has developed what appear to be faint stretch marks along her inner arms and across her shoulders. This is not from weight changes, but from the rapid muscle development that occurred during her intensive Archive training. At first glance they might be mistaken for pale scars, but they have a silvery quality that catches light differently.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nHer hands tell perhaps the most complex story because they have retained the original calluses from cricket farmin, but have been joined by new ones from weapons training. This has created an unusual pattern of toughened skin. Her fingertips retain unusual sensitivity despite the calluses, a remnant of her delicate work with small insects and mechanisms in Espera.\n\n\r\n\n\n\r\nUnlike other desert dwellers, Garnett shows no signs of the chronic dehydration lines or sun damage that would be expected for someone her age. The Archive''s controlled environment seems to have preserved some of her youthful skin quality while her genetics have protected her from typical spore exposure effects. This creates an unsettling contrast where she looks both older and younger than her years simultaneously.", "distinctPhysicalFeatures": null}', '0fe4e254-02d1-4a14-9046-6b3aefe17a89');
INSERT INTO public.saved_items (id, user_id, item_type, item_id, created_at, item_data, notebook_id) VALUES ('54bc376e-b655-43a8-94ca-9f5ec668c572', '33081217', 'character', '1ce382ef-c04e-4737-80a3-d9055cba715f', '2025-10-07 16:59:00.30565', '{"id": "1ce382ef-c04e-4737-80a3-d9055cba715f", "age": 49, "ego": null, "sex": null, "flaw": null, "pets": null, "build": "", "debts": null, "funds": null, "genre": "Fantasy", "likes": "", "vices": null, "accent": null, "allies": null, "assets": null, "family": null, "gender": "Female", "height": "", "legacy": null, "prefix": null, "suffix": "", "userId": "33081217", "weight": "", "defects": null, "dialect": null, "enemies": null, "hobbies": null, "insults": null, "species": "5997d5e7-acf9-4c4f-bbcd-66afc204a336", "charisma": null, "dislikes": null, "eyeColor": "", "imageUrl": "/objects/uploads/c2541f05-992a-42f2-9edd-f4f3aab7436a", "nickname": "", "pronouns": "she/her", "skinTone": "", "strength": null, "swearing": null, "backstory": "", "createdAt": "2025-10-07T16:59:00.279Z", "education": "", "ethnicity": null, "etiquette": null, "farewells": null, "givenName": "Sylvia", "greetings": null, "hairColor": "", "hairStyle": null, "interests": null, "languages": [], "metaphors": null, "mutations": null, "strengths": "", "activities": null, "addictions": null, "conditions": null, "confidence": null, "familyName": "Langford", "maidenName": "", "mainSkills": "", "mannerisms": null, "middleName": "Emily", "motivation": "", "notebookId": "0fe4e254-02d1-4a14-9046-6b3aefe17a89", "occupation": "bcbc4563-bb66-43f7-995c-297ed3ec1d6a", "profession": null, "upbringing": null, "voicePitch": null, "accessories": null, "compliments": null, "dateOfBirth": "", "dateOfDeath": "", "description": "Dr. Sylvia Langford carries the weight of a world that tried to save itself and failed spectacularly. There''s something in the way she holds herself—shoulders perpetually tight, like she''s bracing for the next crisis—that speaks to years of watching green tendrils dismantle civilization one city block at a time.\n\nHer hands tell their own story. Chemical burns have left faint marks across her knuckles, souvenirs from countless failed experiments in the early days when desperation made everyone a little reckless with safety protocols. She still works with an intensity that unsettles some of her colleagues, hunched over microscopes and sample trays for twelve, fourteen, sometimes sixteen hours at a stretch. Sleep has become negotiable.\n\nThe salt flats changed her. There''s a particular kind of paranoia you develop when you''ve lived as a refugee, when you''ve seen what happens to settlements that get complacent. She keeps emergency supplies stashed in odd corners of the bunker—water purification tablets taped under her desk, a go-bag hidden behind filing cabinets. Old habits. Her boys used to tease her about it, back when they were younger and thought their mother was being overcautious.\n\nShe remembers the Mojave nights in Espera with an almost painful clarity. The way the sky stretched endlessly dark and clean, no verdant canopy choking out the stars. How quiet it could be. The bunker''s different—constant hum of ventilation systems, the sterile smell of recycled air. Sometimes she misses the salt and dust, even knowing what they''d fled from.\n\nHer marriage to Milan has weathered more than most. They don''t always agree on her methods, her refusal to consider that maybe the Verdancy can''t be reversed. Maybe shouldn''t be. But he understands the drive, even when it scares him. Even when she forgets to come to bed.\n\nThere''s a photograph she keeps in her lab coat pocket, creased from handling. Her family in Espera, before the Archive recruitment. Everyone''s squinting against the desert sun, Milan''s arm around her waist, the twins making faces at the camera.", "hairTexture": null, "investments": null, "personality": null, "toneOfVoice": null, "wealthClass": null, "workHistory": null, "catchphrases": null, "dependencies": null, "extroversion": null, "familialTies": null, "famousQuotes": "", "heightDetail": null, "hygieneValue": null, "imageCaption": "", "importSource": null, "keyEquipment": null, "mentalHealth": "", "placeOfBirth": "", "placeOfDeath": "", "rememberedBy": null, "behavingStyle": null, "commonPhrases": null, "facialDetails": null, "lackingSkills": null, "proficiencies": null, "secretBeliefs": null, "speakingStyle": null, "typicalAttire": "", "articleContent": null, "characterFlaws": "", "facialFeatures": "", "genderIdentity": "", "honorificTitle": "Dr.", "negativeEvents": null, "religiousViews": null, "worldInfluence": null, "accomplishments": null, "currentLocation": null, "leadershipGroup": null, "particularities": null, "positiveAspects": null, "religiousBelief": "", "behavioralTraits": null, "currentResidence": "", "disposableIncome": null, "frownedUponViews": null, "habitualGestures": null, "identifyingMarks": "", "importExternalId": null, "keyRelationships": null, "lackingKnowledge": null, "overseeingDomain": null, "positionDuration": null, "specialAbilities": "", "specializedItems": null, "strikingFeatures": "", "physicalCondition": "She drinks her coffee black now, not because she likes it but because rationing makes powdered creamer a luxury she won''t justify. Small sacrifices add up.\n\nThe other researchers have learned not to interrupt her before noon. Mornings are for the dangerous work—the live samples, the specimens that still pulse with that sickly bioluminescence. Her hands don''t shake anymore when she handles them. They did once—everyone''s did. But fear becomes mundane when you face it every single day for years on end.\n\nShe''s developed a reputation for being cold. Uncompromising. Someone started a rumour that she cares more about her research than her own sons, which isn''t fair but also isn''t entirely wrong. How do you explain that saving humanity requires a certain detachment? That if she let herself feel the full weight of every loss, every failed trial, every settlement that went dark on the communications network—she''d never get out of bed.\n\nSilvan asked her once why she couldn''t just accept things the way they are now. He was thirteen. Already growing up in a world where the Verdancy was normal, where humanity living underground felt like the natural order. The question haunted her for weeks. Still does, if she''s being honest.\n\nShe has a tell when she''s close to a breakthrough—starts humming under her breath, old songs from before. Classic rock her father used to play. Milan noticed it years ago. The rest of the team has caught on. When Dr. Langford starts humming \"Landslide\" while pipetting samples, everyone gets a little more hopeful. A little more tense.\n\nHer handwriting has gotten worse. Chicken scratch that only her lab assistant can reliably decode. Too many hours gripping instruments, peering through microscopes. The optometrist keeps suggesting she needs reading glasses. She keeps forgetting to get them, or maybe it''s not forgetting. Maybe it''s the same reason she doesn''t schedule the dental work or address the persistent ache in her lower back. Maintenance feels frivolous when the world''s ending in slow motion.\n\nShe lies to Milan sometimes about when she last ate. It''s easier than the lecture, the worried crease between his eyebrows. He''s got enough to worry about.", "sexualOrientation": "", "speechImpediments": null, "intellectualTraits": "", "spiritualPractices": null, "supernaturalPowers": "", "valuesEthicsMorals": "", "genderUnderstanding": null, "physicalDescription": "", "physicalPresentation": null, "languageFluencyAccent": null, "marksPiercingsTattoos": null, "speechParticularities": null, "affiliatedOrganizations": null, "distinctiveBodyFeatures": "", "distinctPhysicalFeatures": null}', '0fe4e254-02d1-4a14-9046-6b3aefe17a89');
